headline: AT&T CEO on potential Trump DEI pressure for $5.75B deal: 'We don't have to roll back anything'
summary: AT&T CEO John Stankey stops short of saying he will bend to any Trump administration demands on DEI if the company wants to close on a new $5.75 billion fiber deal.

headline: T-Mobile or Verizon: Which Telecom Stock Is the Smarter Investment?
summary: VZ's focus on expanding 5G ultra-wideband deployment, customer-focused approach is positive, while healthy demand for postpaid services, strategic buyout and 5G expansion are tailwinds for TMUS.
